  "texts": [
    "Additionally, hyperspectral imaging faces challenges like multicollinearity and incomplete or noisy data, complicating product characterization (Wambugu et al. 2021).",
    "While recent developments in snapshot HSI technologies have improved the potential for real-time spectral image acquisition, these systems often compromise on spatial and spectral resolution.",
    "Finding a balance between performance and practicality in HSI systems still remains a crucial focus of ongoing research and development.",
    "The high cost, complexity of equipment, low spatial resolution and limited image availability have all hindered the widespread adoption of traditional HSI systems.",
    "To overcome these limitations, there is growing interest in developing methods to reconstruct hyperspectral data from standard RGB images (Li et al. 2017; Arad et al. 2020; Zhao et al. 2020b; Zhang et al. 2022)."
